args:
When the party makes for Hinomoto in order to
learn about the new evil that bedevils them,
the Mukuroshu break the barrier around their
base and claim it. That night, the dragon who
leads the Mukuroshu, Tsukuyomi, finally
descends upon the world...
The way is clear... This is our chance!\nEight-span Mirror, shine forth your\nheavenly light upon the world!
The dead vanished! Does this mean...?
Yes, I think we stopped the Yomi chi\nthat was seeping into Alberia.
Not yet. Though the flow was stemmed,\nit is but a temporary measure.
We will only have true resolution when\nthe gates to the Realm of the Dead are\nbarred shut once more.
I KNEW there was a stupid catch!\nOkay, so how do we do that?
We must find the Underworld Key that\noriginally unlocked the gates and use it\nto seal them anew.
Then we must make for Hinomoto,\nwhere the Realm of the Dead was opened.
You may rest assured I will see the matter\ndone, Prince {player_name}.
Actually, I was thinking we would\ndo it as a team.
I can't sit around and do nothing\nwhen Alberia might be in danger.
Then let us go together. I will ferry us\nthere with the power of teleportation\nbestowed upon me by Lady Amaterasu.
(I worried I wasn't helping here, but I\nactually made things WORSE! The general\nis never gonna acknowledge me now.)
(But I'm not giving up! I'll just have to\nwork that much harder from here on out\nand prove my worth to him.)
I'll become the Tiger clan leader and catch\nup to the General, whatever it takes!
Wow, that teleportation dealie was FAST!\nSo I guess this is Hinomoto, huh? Neat!
We ain't here for sightseeing, Notte.\nKeep your head on a swivel.
Look! The shogun's forces are already\nfighting the Mukuroshu! Hinomoto has\nbecome a battlefield...
Don't worry, Izumo!\nGeneral, let's hurry up and help 'em!
No. Our task is to find the Underworld Key.\nWe cannot afford to be seen by the\nMukuroshu here.

Fix your eyes on the bigger picture, Yuki.
Some fight to defend cities, while others
carry out secret orders. Each is but a part
of a war's greater whole.
Now, let us begin our search.\nFirst, we need...
A base. Correct, Lord Shingen?\nPlease leave the matter to me.
I cast a stealth barrier upon the area.\nSo long as we remain within this bamboo\ngrove, the enemy cannot find us.
The spell can only be released from within,\nwhich means we are safe inside.
As ever, you've given me precisely what I\nwanted before I'd even said a word.\nYou truly do know my every thought.
And all else about you, my lordâ€”for I am\never watching you each hour of the day\nand season of the year.
I'm not certain ï¼‚dedicationï¼‚ is the word I\nwould choose for such behavior...
Come, everyone. There's a small hunter's\ncottage nearby that we can use as our\nbase of operations.
*sigh* We've been here for two days and\nhave yet to discover a single tenable lead.
If we don't find the Underworld Key soon,\nall of this will... Hmm?
I didn't sleep all night because Luca kept\nshouting in his sleep. I did not even know\nsuch a thing was possible...
How am I supposed to search for the key\nin such a state?
Ha ha ha! My apologies if I startled you,\nbut I couldn't help but laugh. Were you\nreally just speaking to the mirror?
Y-yes, I fear it's a rather embarrassing\nhabit of mine. Please forgive anything\nyou may have overheard.
Oh, I used to do the same thing. When\nmy master went off to battle without me,\nI would grouse to the castle statues.
It may be a bit silly as you say, but it also\nhelped me feel less alone. Do you find it\ndoes much the same for you?
Well...yes. I suppose it does. I rarely have\nanyone else to talk to back in the palace.

Yes, I imagine other children your age
mostly spend their time playing outside.
Well, if you need someone to listen,
I would be happy to help.
You're very kind. But as one tasked with\nspreading the word of Lady Amaterasu,\nI am not to speak my own mind outside.
I ask that you forget the embarrassing\nscene you witnessed here and help me\ncontinue the search for the key.
(He's really just a boy beneath all that\nduty, and I worry he'll wear himself thin\nat this rate.)
Yukimura, reporting back from my scouting\nmissionâ€”and the report is ï¼‚Blech.ï¼‚
Gya! You're caked head to toe in mud!\nHave you been out scouting all night?
Uh huh. But I need to check even further\nout, so I'll head in the other direction just\nas soon as I...have some...break...fast...
Ugh. I'm sorry you had to waste time on\nme...but I'm good now! Ready to roll!
Don't push yourself, Yukimura. You have a\nwhole night's worth of missed rest that you\nneed to make up for.
Aw, this doesn't count as pushing myself.\nI'm feeling AWESOME! Honest I am!
If you force things now and faint again,\nit will only cost more time in the end.
But if I don't work harder, the general\nwill never acknowledge me!
Admire him? I want to BE him! I want to\ncatch up to the great man he is and have\nhim name me as his successor!
And the future Tiger Wyrmclan leader can't\nlet something like this slow her down.
Actually, about that. You were born in a\nMonkey clan household, right? Can you\neven become the Tiger clan's leader?
For sure! I mean, probably? Apparently\nI've got Monkey AND Tiger blood in me.
Oh? I wasn't aware that the Wyrmclans\nintermarried like that.
Oh, they don't. Well, hardly ever, anyway.\nThey said I'm the first kid who ever came\nfrom parents of two different clans.
It kinda ruined the relationship between\nthe clans, actuallyâ€”which is why I grew\nup as a hostage.
So you were some sort of political pawn?
I guess? I don't really know the details.\nBack when I was a hostage, nobody told\nme anything, and I didn't ask.
It sounds like being born to a military clan\nof Hinomoto is a hard life, though it seems\nyou're something of an exceptional case.
Aw, it really wasn't that badâ€”especially\nonce the general rescued me!
Wait, Shingen rescued you? How didâ€”
One oughtn't bore others with dreary tales\nof personal matters. My apologies for that,\nPrince {player_name}.
Actually, I found it all really interesting.\nHow exactly did you manage to solve the\nconflict between the two clans?
It was not so pretty a thing as to be\ncalled ï¼‚resolution.ï¼‚

From the time I was a child, I was ill-liked
by my father. So much so, in fact, that he
planned to pass the leadership of our clan
to my younger brother instead.

But the citizens and vassals of the Tiger
clan suffered greatly under my father's
rule, so I chose my people over my
family...
And lead a rebellion against him.
That must have been very difficult.

Indeed it was. But in the end, it quelled
the fight between Wyrmclans and bought
Yuki her freedom, so I've not once looked
back upon my decision with regret.
Man, I'll never forget the day the general\nfirst took me outside. I was ready to follow\nhim pretty much anywhere!
And it seems like you have.
Yep! And I'm keeping my eyes fixed on him\nuntil the day he finally acknowledges me.
Tireless effort! Daily improvement!\nThose are the tools in my arsenal!
You've no need to become as I am, Yuki.
You have a form of strength all your own,\none thatâ€”
The barrier is broken. I will go investigate\nthe situation at once, Lord Shingen.
But I thought the barrier could only be\nremoved from within, so whoâ€”

You are the Wyrmclan leaders and the
Alberian prince, yes? We already have
your friends captive, so I would advise you
not to try anything clever.
Nnngh! Let me go, you ruffians!
Sorry, everybody. I thought the barrier was\nimpenetrable, so I sorta took a little nap.
I see little choice in the matter,\nPrince {player_name}.
Agreed. We'll go quietly for now.
The moon hangs low and full...\nTo light the revenant's return...
Hey, so what's with the creepy\nsong-and-dance number?
It is a rite of returning. Tonight, this world\nwelcomes our master from the Realm of\nthe Dead. Lady Tsukuyomi's advent is nigh!
A dragon, and leader of the Mukuroshu.
The Mukuroshu is run by a DRAGON?!
Yes. The shogunate has toiled in secret to\nfind her by any means possible, but all\ntheir efforts came to naught.
The reason for that now lies clear, as does\nthe reason why the Mukuroshu sought to\nopen the gates.
Even I never dreamed Tsukuyomi might be\nhiding within the Realm of the Dead.
You can stop nothing now, old man.\nThe full moon provides a fitting stage\nfor Lady Tsukuyomi's return!
I bid you watch her glorious comingâ€”\nand with it, the final dawn of the\ndetestable shogunate!
Come forth, mistress! Let the flesh and\nblood before you be your welcoming feast!\nAaaaah ha ha ha ha ha!
The chi surrounding us is trembling.\nI think Tsukuyomi is...
Ah, the moon... How I have pined\nfor the living world's moon.
It has been far, far too long.
Come, lowly humans! Let us mark the\noccasion with a moonwatching revel!
